Be sure to check out the plans for these tiles item no. ANIMAL__A_Z as well to make them yourself!
- - - - - - -
#TeamTOOLSTODAY
- - - - - - -

node.text:
My favorite method for filling small cracks and knots is Starbond Adhesives Black CA glue, item #K2, and the accelerator, item #A6, both available on our website! It is so quick and easy as the accelerator dries the glue within 30 seconds so you can get it sanded and move on with the project.  No waiting hours for epoxy to cure!
- -

Making the #TTnationalParkSign on the Stepcraft Q.408 4'x8' CNC machine, available on our website, using @corafoam_hdusigns 20lb HDU foam. **What do you think of how it turned out?
- - - - - - -
#TeamTOOLSTODAY
- - - - - - -
The plans for this project are available on our website item no. PARK_SIGN. I started off by applying some Oramask 813 to the prepainted piece.  I the carved into it using Amana Tool #RC-1102 90° Insert carbide ‘V’-Groove bit featuring 1-1/2" diameter, 3/4" cut height and 1/2” shank available from @toolstoday!
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 40ipm
Plunge Rate: 20ipm
Depth per pass: .5"
- - - - - - -
The bit cut insanely cleanly through the Oramask 813, also available on our website, and HDU foam leaving no cleanup work needed at all!  The piece was then painted with General Finishes Snow White milk paint, available on our website.
- - - - - - -
I then switched out for the Amana Tool #46202-K 1/4" Spektra™ coated downcut bit to do all of the clearing out on the flat bottom V-carve.
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 120ipm
Plunge Rate: 60ipm
Depth per pass: .25"
- - - - - - -
I then switched out to the Amana Tool #RC-1148 60° insert carbide V-Groove bit to do all of the fine detail work for a nice clean cut!
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 40ipm
Plunge Rate: 20ipm
Max Depth: .25"
- - - - - - -
I then switched out for the #46315-K 1/4" Spektra™ coated upcut bit to do the profile cutting.
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 120ipm
Plunge Rate: 60ipm
Depth per pass: .25"
- - - - - - -
The piece was taped off and painted and keyhol slots were made using the Amana Tool #45650 3/8" diameter keyhole bit.
- - - - - - -
RPM: 18,000
Feed Rate: 100ipm
Plunge Rate: 50ipm
Depth per pass: .325"
- - - - - - -
The piece was cut free at the bandsaw and flush trimmed with the Amana Tool #47092 1/4" diameter 1" cut height bit.  A chamfer was added on the back side with the Amana Tool #49400 45° 1-1/4" diameter chamfer bit.  The rest of the painting was completed and the piece was finished with Minwax Sparurethane in satin.
- - - - - - -

#TeamTOOLSTODAY

Installing and setting up the new sliding cross cut table attachment, item no. TSA-SA48, on the SawStop table saw for the first time with the Amana Tool #610601C 10" diameter 60T Prestige general purpose blade, all available on the @toolstoday website, to cut down this block of cherry counter top for a cutting board project.
- - - - - - -
#TeamTOOLSTODAY
- - - - - - -
This sliding table made cross cutting this 24" block a breeze, something I couldn't have done with a standard miter gauge!  Really excited to have this in the shop, it'll make cutting down full sheet goods to size much easier!
